# Project Integrity

## Directory Structure — Never Break

```
src/
  mlmodel.py          # orchestrateur: train, optimize, infer, save
  models/             # one file per model class (inherits BaseModel)
params/
  ml_params.yaml      # ML config (model, optuna, threshold)
dataset/              # read-only, never modify
notebooks/            # one per author/experiment
outputs/
  res_perf/           # performance artifacts (metrics, plots, feature importances)
  submissions/        # submission CSVs only
```

## Rules

- `dataset/` is **read-only** — never write, move, or delete files there
- `src/mlmodel.py` orchestrates training, optimization, inference and saving via `MLModel` class
- New models go in `src/models/` following `BaseModel` interface
- `params/ml_params.yaml` stays minimal — no hardcoded paths elsewhere
- Submissions always go to `outputs/submissions/`
- Performance artifacts (metrics, plots, feature importances) go to `outputs/res_perf/`
- Never commit trained model artifacts (`.joblib`) — already in `.gitignore`
